%F A002478 a(n) = a(n-1) + 2*a(n-2) + a(n-3).
%F A002478 a(n) = Sum_{k=0..n} binomial(2*n-2*k, k). - _Paul Barry_, Nov 13 2004
%F A002478 a(n) = Sum_{k=0..floor(n/2)} Sum_{j=0..n-k} C(j, n-k-j)*C(j, k). - _Paul Barry_, Nov 09 2005
%F A002478 a(n) = Sum_{k=0..n} C(2*k,n-k) = Sum_{k=0..n} C(n,k)*C(3*k,n)/C(3*k,k). - _Paul Barry_, Feb 04 2006
%F A002478 a(n) = A000930(n) + 2*Sum_{i=0..n-2} a(i)*A000930(n-2-i). - _Michael Tulskikh_, Jun 07 2020
%e A002478 a(3)=6 as there is one tiling of a 3 X 3 region with only 1 X 1 tiles, 4 tilings with exactly one 2 X 2 tile and 1 tiling consisting of the 3 X 3 tile.
